This term in Japanese is nearly as broad in use as {{cog|en|egg}}, indicating an egg as [[lay|laid]] by various [[oviparous]] [[organism]]s, and egg as used in [[cooking]]. For the more specific biological sense of {{m|en|ovum}}, see {{m|ja|卵子|tr=ranshi}}.

